headline: Is Interactive Brokers Still Attractive After 36% YTD Surge Amid Mixed Valuation Signals?
summary: Thinking about whether to hold, buy, or maybe cash in your gains on Interactive Brokers Group? You are in good company. This stock has been a star performer over the long haul, with a staggering 393.7% return over five years and even notching up 94.2% over the past twelve months. Yet, in the shorter term, the last seven days and 30 days have brought modest dips, down 0.3% and 2.2% respectively. Year-to-date, shares are still up a robust 36.4%.
